        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="effective-date">Effective Date: October 5, 2025</p>
        
        <p>SkyNet Tech ("we," "our," or "us") operates the Ultimate Network Tools mobile application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you use our App.</p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        
        <h3>1.1 Information You Provide</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Network Queries:</strong> When you use our network diagnostic tools (Ping, Traceroute, Port Scanner, Domain Resolver, etc.), you input IP addresses, domains, or URLs. This information is processed locally on your device and is not stored or transmitted to our servers.</li>
            <li><strong>App Preferences:</strong> We store your app settings, theme preferences, and favorite tools locally on your device to enhance your user experience.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>1.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We collect device identifiers, operating system version, and app version for analytics and advertising purposes.</li>
            <li><strong>Advertising ID:</strong> We use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect your Advertising ID to serve personalized ads.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Firebase Analytics collects anonymous usage statistics such as which features you use, app crashes, and session duration to help us improve the App.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use the collected information for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To provide and maintain the App's functionality</li>
            <li>To display advertisements through Google AdMob</li>
            <li>To analyze app performance and user behavior through Firebase Analytics</li>
            <li>To improve user experience and fix bugs</li>
            <li>To process in-app purchases (Pro version)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Data Storage and Processing</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Your app preferences, theme settings, and favorite tools are stored locally on your device and are not transmitted to our servers.</li>
            <li><strong>Network Queries:</strong> All network diagnostic queries (domains, IPs, URLs you test) are processed in real-time and are not stored or logged.</li>
            <li><strong>No User Accounts:</strong> We do not require user registration or maintain user accounts.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>We use the following third-party services that may collect information:</p>
        
        <h3>4.1 Google AdMob</h3>
        <p>We use Google AdMob to display advertisements. AdMob may collect and use your Advertising ID and device information to serve personalized ads. For more information, please review Google's Privacy Policy at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a></p>

        <h3>4.2 Firebase Analytics</h3>
        <p>We use Firebase Analytics to understand how users interact with our App. Firebase collects anonymous usage data including app opens, feature usage, and crash reports. For more information, visit <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank">https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy</a></p>

        <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>We do not sell, trade, or transfer your information to third parties except:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>To third-party service providers (Google AdMob, Firebase) as described above</li>
            <li>When required by law or to protect our rights</li>
            <li>With your explicit consent</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p>Our App is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us.</p>

        <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Advertising Opt-Out:</strong> You can limit ad tracking by adjusting your device settings (iOS: Settings > Privacy > Advertising > Limit Ad Tracking).</li>
            <li><strong>Data Deletion:</strong> You can delete all locally stored data by uninstalling the App.</li>
            <li><strong>Pro Version:</strong> Purchasing the Pro version removes advertisements and reduces data collection.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Data Security</h2>
        <p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure.</p>

        <h2>9. International Users</h2>
        <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. By using the App, you consent to such transfers.</p>

        <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Effective Date" above.</p>

        <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
        <div class="contact">
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:</p>
            <p><strong>Email:</strong> skyguardsx@gmail.com</p>
            <p><strong>Developer:</strong> SkyNet Tech</p>
